SSyynnooppssiiss
       hvgen highlevel_file

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The  hvgen  command generates a Reliant configuration file
       from a high-level representation (.hl description file) of
       the  configuration  and  a set of standard template files.
       Specify the name of the high-level input file.

       It is important to remember the following: Never  generate
       the  file with the same name as the running configuration.
       If the generation fails because /tmp or /var/tmp  are  too
       small,  set the environment variable TMPDIR to a directory
       which has more space and compile again.  The .hl file must
       exist in /usr/opt/reliant/build.

EExxaammpplleess
       The  following  example  shows  a high-level configuration
       file: Cluster {
           { SYSA,SYSB }                       // nodes
           { }                                 // attributes
               Application                     //  under  control
       of Reliant
               {
                   App1
                   {  SYSA,SYSB  }                             //
       priority
                   { AutoStartUp  AutoSwitchOver  }            //
       attributes
                   {                                           //
       resources
                           Mount( /dir1 Volume( sharedg  volshare
       ) vxfs )
                   }
               } } The following command generates the configura-
       tion: hvgen newconfig.hl

FFiilleess
       /usr/opt/reliant/etc/templates/*

